{"author":{"id":"977fec8a59c245f25e0e700fa290ef50836c624572869487e9e47fedc85061ee"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1492608469,"nonce":"U6bmEjQpgAxn7g5KjIMvYfrc1HM=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI5NTI2OTk1OQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1262#issuecomment-295269959"},"message":"\u003e Can we systematically check all the legacy packages to ensure everything is present in bioconda (and add older versions to bioconda as needed)?\n\nI think @bgruening had been working towards this, and initially I was also thinking that would be important. We do have an IUC conda channel that we can use for \"dirty\" packages. But currently I think it may be wiser to work towards \"future-facing reproducibility\", and assume that few people are going to re-install old tools with old packages (which will still be possible! We're just discouraging people from investing time in these packages, be it an admin that installs a legacy toolshed package when conda would be available, or a developer that updates outdated packages).","files":null}]}